title: SS Canberra
author: Unknown
pages:
The SS Canberra was
an Australian/British
cruiseliner that when
the Falklands conflict
began was used by
the British to
transport 3 Commando
Brigade along with
mean from 40,42,45
commando brigade and
also 3Para. 2400 of
these soldiers
belonged to the
crutial first wave. It

was also ran by a 400
man volunteer crew
